dcterms:description: The MUSK1 dataset is used to predict the impact of drugs given the molecule conformations. Each bag consists of several conformations of the same molecule, with a positive label if at least one conformation has the desired drug effect.
dcterms:title: MUSK1

dcterms:description: The MUSK2 dataset is similar to MUSK1 and is used to predict the impact of drugs given the molecule conformations. Each bag consists of several conformations of the same molecule, with a positive label if at least one conformation has the desired drug effect.
dcterms:title: MUSK2

dcterms:creator: S. Andrews
I. Tsochantaridis
T. Hofmann
dcterms:description: The FOX dataset is used to identify if the target animal is presented in a bag. Each bag consists of a set of features extracted from segments of an image, with positive bags indicating the presence of the animal.
dcterms:title: FOX

dcterms:creator: S. Andrews
I. Tsochantaridis
T. Hofmann
dcterms:description: The TIGER dataset is used for identifying if the target animal is presented in a bag, similar to the FOX dataset. Each bag consists of features extracted from segments of an image.
dcterms:title: TIGER

dcterms:creator: S. Andrews
I. Tsochantaridis
T. Hofmann
dcterms:description: The ELEPHANT dataset is used to identify if the target animal is presented in a bag, similar to the FOX and TIGER datasets. Each bag consists of features extracted from segments of an image.
dcterms:title: ELEPHANT

dcterms:description: The CAMELYON16 dataset is a publicly available WSI dataset for detecting metastatic breast cancer in lymph node tissue. It consists of 399 WSIs, with binary labels indicating the presence or absence of metastatic cancer.
dcterms:title: CAMELYON16

dcterms:creator: B. Li
Y. Li
K. W. Eliceiri
dcterms:description: The TCGA-NSCLC dataset is used for identifying two sub-types of lung cancer: lung squamous cell carcinoma and lung adenocarcinoma. It consists of 1,037 diagnostic WSIs.
dcterms:title: TCGA-NSCLC
